{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bad5110d-26cd-4eea-bd7d-8bd4287daad5","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general recipe for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Register your package on NuGet.org for trusted publishing\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a **GitHub Actions** publisher: set the repo owner, repo name, and optionally a workflow filename / environment\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Remove:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push ... --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n**Add these changes:**\n\n```yaml\n# Job-level: request an OIDC token\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for OIDC\n  contents: read\n\nsteps:\n  # 1. Install the NuGet trusted-publish CLI tool (one-time)\n  - name: Install trusted-publish tool\n    run: dotnet tool install --global NuGetKeyVaultSignTool || true\n    # Actually, the native support uses dotnet nuget trusted-publish\n\n  # 2. Obtain the OIDC token and push\n  - name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n    run: |\n      dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n        --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n        --trusted-publishing\n```\n\n### Key changes summarized\n\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | No secret needed |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` permission |\n| `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | `--trusted-publishing` flag |\n\n### 3. Delete the old secret\nOnce verified, remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from **Settings → Secrets**.\n\n> **Note:** NuGet trusted publishing is relatively new. Check the [NuGet docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/nuget/nuget-org/trusted-publishing) for the latest CLI flags — the exact `dotnet nuget push` flag name may vary by SDK version. If you share your workflow file, I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dddbec68-cc23-4f2d-8877-b23b52b173a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Since there's no existing workflow file to examine, I'll provide guidance based on what they described.","outputTokens":613,"requestId":"5C4D:3F4A4A:F58043:1351A4C:69FFD890"},"id":"8f9e00ab-7be8-4ad3-afa1-ac2ca56e115a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:14.217Z","parentId":"96696f1f-56c5-42b6-920d-862a4a4f1f31"}
